45">Computer science</keyword><keyword weight="0.46617">Knowledge management</keyword><keyword weight="0.46351">Systems design</keyword><keyword weight="0.44904">Humanâ€“computer interaction</keyword><keyword weight="0.50197">Engineering design process</keyword><keyword weight="0.0">Workplace studies</keyword></keywords><publisher>Kluwer Academic Publishers</publisher><abstract>We have considered the role of workplace studies from the CSCW literature which are intended to inform system design and implementation. We present a critique of these studies, categorised according to which phase of the design process they most inform, and discuss the tensions between providing explanatory accounts and usable design recommendations, the pressures on fieldworkers to provide both, the purposes different approaches serve, and the transition from fieldwork to system design.</abstract></paper>